00:49:41.119 --> 00:49:43.160
But you don't necessarily
know who that person is

00:49:43.160 --> 00:49:44.920
or who the sender is.

00:49:44.920 --> 00:49:47.270
So that obfuscates the
individual's identity,

00:49:47.270 --> 00:49:50.255
which in a lot of situations,
is a very good thing.

00:49:50.255 --> 00:49:52.380
The other question though
that's really interesting

00:49:52.380 --> 00:49:56.350
that you mentioned is the
origination right of the asset

00:49:56.350 --> 00:50:00.830
and how do you secure privacy
for whatever that asset is.

00:50:00.830 --> 00:50:03.300
And this is an interesting
point for the financial services

00:50:03.300 --> 00:50:04.120
industry.

00:50:04.120 --> 00:50:04.990
We have bitcoin.

00:50:04.990 --> 00:50:05.630
We have ether.

00:50:05.630 --> 00:50:06.838
These are public blockchains.

00:50:06.838 --> 00:50:10.700
But if all financial assets,
like stocks and bonds,

00:50:10.700 --> 00:50:12.410
are going to move
onto this platform,

00:50:12.410 --> 00:50:14.120
someone's got to issue them.

00:50:14.120 --> 00:50:17.440
Maybe it's the Bank of England
issues a digital pound,

00:50:17.440 --> 00:50:19.854
or Apple issues a
digital share certificate

00:50:19.854 --> 00:50:20.770
using this technology.

00:50:20.770 --> 00:50:22.103
But someone's got to issue them.

00:50:22.103 --> 00:50:26.440
So the interesting thing there
is that intermediaries are not

00:50:26.440 --> 00:50:26.940
going away.

00:50:26.940 --> 00:50:30.040
Maybe intermediaries just
change their name to originators

00:50:30.040 --> 00:50:33.420
because someone's got to
start building this platform--

00:50:33.420 --> 00:50:37.425
or rather moving assets into
a native digital format.

00:50:37.425 --> 00:50:39.300
And actually I think
that's a big opportunity

00:50:39.300 --> 00:50:42.710
for big financial firms
to do, essentially

00:50:42.710 --> 00:50:43.799
So they're not going away.

