00:53:05.249 --> 00:53:07.540
AUDIENCE: So if I can come
back to the privacy question

00:53:07.540 --> 00:53:08.800
from a different angle,
I think might have

00:53:08.800 --> 00:53:10.049
different backgrounds on this.

00:53:12.640 --> 00:53:15.400
An awful lot of sort
of investigative work,

00:53:15.400 --> 00:53:18.040
in terms of the criminality,
which you alluded to earlier,

00:53:18.040 --> 00:53:19.050
is following the money.

00:53:19.050 --> 00:53:21.020
Are we just going to accept
that we can't follow the money

00:53:21.020 --> 00:53:22.190
anymore in the new world?

00:53:22.190 --> 00:53:22.890
ALEX TAPSCOTT: Well,
actually I think

00:53:22.890 --> 00:53:24.973
that it helps you to follow
the money much better.

00:53:24.973 --> 00:53:28.500
$2 and 1/2 trillion a year
of crime is done with cash.

00:53:28.500 --> 00:53:30.250
And cash is the ultimate
bear instrument.

00:53:30.250 --> 00:53:31.490
You know, it's a paper bill.

00:53:31.490 --> 00:53:34.080
You can't trace back cash.

00:53:34.080 --> 00:53:36.920
It's harder to track payments
made in bitcoin than it is

00:53:36.920 --> 00:53:39.670
to, say, Visa
payments or something.

00:53:39.670 --> 00:53:42.080
But it's a lot easier
than it is with cash.

00:53:42.080 --> 00:53:44.890
And because you have this
unbroken record of where money

00:53:44.890 --> 00:53:46.840
is moved, generally
speaking, you

00:53:46.840 --> 00:53:48.500
combine that with
other policing,

00:53:48.500 --> 00:53:51.350
and you can actually stop
crime much easier than you can

00:53:51.350 --> 00:53:54.460
with cash, which is why like
Mark Carney in his mansion

00:53:54.460 --> 00:53:57.690
house speech last two
weeks ago said that this

00:53:57.690 --> 00:53:59.460
could help to reduce crime.

00:53:59.460 --> 00:54:01.432
Because the less cash
there is in the system,

00:54:01.432 --> 00:54:03.790
the less opportunities
there are for criminals.

00:54:03.790 --> 00:54:06.010
But also after the Mt.

00:54:06.010 --> 00:54:10.390
Gox and the Silk Road issues,
law enforcement agents

00:54:10.390 --> 00:54:14.080
in the US began to call
bitcoin prosecution futures

00:54:14.080 --> 00:54:17.450
because you could actually
kind of identify down

00:54:17.450 --> 00:54:20.250
the road when you could
catch someone based on when

00:54:20.250 --> 00:54:21.590
the transaction occurred.

00:54:21.590 --> 00:54:25.560
So not to say that
criminals won't use it.

00:54:25.560 --> 00:54:28.130
Malware happens now
increasingly with bitcoin

00:54:28.130 --> 00:54:30.450
more so than any
other payment method.

00:54:30.450 --> 00:54:32.540
And that'll be an
issue, but it's actually

00:54:32.540 --> 00:54:33.660
a superior alternative.

00:54:33.660 --> 00:54:35.726
And I think if law
enforcement's engaged

00:54:35.726 --> 00:54:38.100
and intelligent on the issue,
it could be a tool for them

00:54:38.100 --> 00:54:39.317
as well.

